<HEADLINE>
<P>
AL'S RIVER CAT WIRES 'SLEW FIELD FOR EASY THREE-LENGTH VICTORY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Golden Eagle Farm's 7-5 favorite Al's River Cat took command at the start and 
never looked back to win the $56,600 Tsunami Slew Handicap by three lengths 
under jockey Alex Solis Friday night at Hollywood Park. 
</P>
<P>
 It was the third win in eight starts for Al's River Cat, who earned $31,850 
and gave Solis and trainer Lewis Cenicola their second victories of the night. 
</P>
<P>
 Al's River Cat, a 3-year-old Kentucky-bred son of Riverman, paid $4.80, $3.40 
and $2.60. Troyalty prompted the pace in second along the rail early, dropped 
back to third on the turn, then finished gamely to take second. 
</P>
<P>
 Troyalty, ridden by Corey Black, returned $3.80 and $2.80. Sharp Try rallied 
from far back to gain third, one length behind Troyalty, and paid $3 to show. 
</P>
<P>
 Al's River Cat covered 5 1/2 furlongs on a firm turf course in 1:02 1/5 under 
117 pounds. 
</P>
<P>
 Ocean Indien, Don Icecapade, Windwood Lad, Feliz Hora and College Town 
completed the order of finish. 
</P>
<P>
 Al's River Cat has never failed to earn a check in eight starts and his 
earnings now stand at $92,550. 
</P>
