<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP ROUNDUP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 In other Olympic League matches: 
</P>
<P>
 Capistrano Valley Christian 3, La Mirada 2 -- Mike Mattson had 16 kills for 
host Capistrano Valley Christian (7-8, 3-7), which won, 15-11, 15-4, 15-17, 
4-15, 15-3. 
</P>
<P>
 In the Pacific Coast League: 
</P>
<P>
 Laguna Beach 3, Estancia 0 -- The fourth-ranked Artists won their eighth 
consecutive league title with a 15-4, 15-11, 15-6 victory. Dan Styles led 
Laguna Beach (15-1, 10-0) with 15 kills. Teammates Beau Bianchi and Szilard 
Kovacs added 14 and 13. Setter Kurt Nelson got 51 assists. No. 10 Estancia (8-2 
in league) finished second. 
</P>
<P>
 Trabuco Hills 3, Costa Mesa 0 -- Bryan Schelin and Steve Carter each had eight 
kills to lead Trabuco Hills to a 15-12, 15-5, 15-2 victory. Chris Congo had 
five aces for the Mustangs (7-8, 6-4), who clinched third place. 
</P>
<P>
 In the South Coast League: 
</P>
<P>
 Dana Hills 3, San Clemente 1 -- Jeremy Darner had 27 kills and Bob Hefty 26 
for visiting Dana Hills (11-4, 7-3), which won, 15-4, 12-15, 15-13, 15-9. San 
Clemente is 7-3 in league. 
</P>
<P>
 In Sea View League boys' tennis: 
</P>
<P>
 Santa Margarita 12 2/3, Newport Harbor 8 1/3 -- Kent Policky and Andy Tsu 
swept at doubles, 6-4, 6-2, 6-2, for Santa Margarita, which captured fourth 
place in league. Santa Margarita will apply for an at-large berth to the 
Southern Section playoffs. 
</P>
<P>
 Geoff Abrams did not lose a game at singles for visiting Newport Harbor. Santa 
Margarita finishes the season 11-10 overall and 8-7 in league; Newport Harbor 
finishes 10-11 and 7-8. 
</P>
<P>
 In Academy League softball: 
</P>
<P>
 St. Margaret's 12, Liberty Christian 1 (5, mercy) -- St. Margaret's clinched 
the Academy League title. The Tartans finished the season with an undefeated 
league record, 11-3, 7-0. Liberty Christian committed six errors in first 
inning. 
</P>
<P>
 In the Sea View League: 
</P>
<P>
 Irvine 4, Santa Margarita 3 (12) -- With two outs, Amy Young tripled in the 
winning run for Irvine (15-9, 9-3). Young also pitched all 12 innings for the 
victory. 
</P>
<P>
 Woodbridge 7, Newport Harbor 2 -- Alison Johnsen had two hits, three stolen 
bases and scored two runs, and Lizzie Lemire had two hits and two RBIs for host 
Woodbridge (19-7, 10-2), ranked ninth. 
</P>
<P>
 In the South Coast League: 
</P>
<P>
 San Clemente 5, Capistrano Valley 1 -- San Clemente (9-12-1, 4-4) took 
advantage of six Capistrano Valley errors to win. Jodi Morris had two hits for 
visiting Capistrano Valley (13-8, 4-4). 
</P>
<P>
 In the Sunset League: 
</P>
<P>
 Fountain Valley 12, Edison 0 (5) -- Lynea Backlund was four for four with two 
RBIs for Fountain Valley (13-8-1, 9-3). 
</P>
<P>
 Marina 14, Santa Ana 4 -- Lynette Velazquez hit a grand slam in the fourth 
inning to lead top-ranked Marina (18-2, 10-1). Santa Ana (2-20, 0-12) led, 4-1, 
after three innings, but the Vikings scored eight runs in the top of the fourth 
to go ahead for good. 
</P>
