<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIRECTOR RICHARD RUSH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Having had the privilege of being directed by Richard Rush in "The Stunt Man," 
I find The Times' comments regarding him to be, at best, unfathomable ("Who's 
Got the Right to 'Color' Final Cut?," April 23). 
</P>
<P>
 The Richard Rush I know and worked with is a man of impeccable integrity, 
ferocious perfectionism and loyalty. How these traits can somehow be perceived 
as character flaws is beyond my comprehension. I applaud his "24-hours-a-day, 
7-days-a-week" dedication to a film into which he has poured his blood, sweat 
and soul. STEVE RAILSBACK 
</P>
