<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEST VALLEY FOCUS: CANOGA PARK; SHOW TO RAISE FUNDS FOR DAMAGED CHURCH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By KAY HWANGBO 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Parishioners at St. Joseph the Worker Church will hold a variety show May 21 
to raise money to renovate their quake-damaged church. 
</P>
<P>
 The Catholic church at 19803 Sherman Way in Canoga Park suffered about 
$200,000 in losses in the temblor, according to Pastor Jim Gehl.Significant 
damage was caused to a 5,000-pipe organ, the bell tower and the ceiling. 
</P>
<P>
 The show, "Shake, Rattle and Roll," will feature singing, dancing, musical 
acts and actors performing two scenes from the musical comedy "Sister Act." 
With tickets going for $3 a person, organizers say they are less concerned with 
making money than they are with restoring parish morale. 
</P>
<P>
 "We don't expect to raise big bucks from this, but we hope to bolster people's 
spirits and come together as a parish family," Gehl said. "We're just going to 
have fun." 
</P>
<P>
 The event will be held at Msgr. Greene Hall at 7 p.m. For information, call 
(818) 341-6634. KAY HWANGBO 
</P>
