<P>
COUNTYWIDE FOCUS: VOTERS HAVE 3 DAYS TO REGISTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * Deadline: Registration deadline is Monday. 
</P>
<P>
 * Requirements: To register, you must be a U. S. citizen, at least 18 years 
old and a California resident at least 29 days before the election. 
</P>
<P>
 * Forms: Registration forms can be obtained by calling the Ventura County 
Elections Division office at 654-2664. The elections office is at 800 S. 
Victoria Ave., in the lower plaza of the Hall of Administration. Office hours 
are 7:30 a.m. to 5:30 p.m. Mondays through Thursdays. Forms can also be picked 
up at most fire stations, city halls, post offices, libraries, chambers of 
commerce and the state Department of Motor Vehicles. 
</P>
<P>
 * Absentee ballots: Applications to vote absentee are on the back page of the 
sample ballot. They may also be obtained in person or by sending a written 
request to the Elections Division, County Government Center, 800 S. Victoria 
Ave., Ventura 93009. Written applications for absentee ballots must be received 
in the office by 5:30 p.m. May 31. 
</P>
<P>
 Source: Ventura County Registrar of Voters 
</P>
