<HEADLINE>
<P>
FEMA APPLICATION DEADLINE EXTENDED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The deadline to apply for disaster assistance for the Jan. 17 earthquake has 
been extended 60 days, a FEMA spokesperson said Friday. 
</P>
<P>
 Disaster relief agencies are continuing to receive more than 1,600 individual 
assistance applications daily, said Federal Emergency Management Agency 
spokesperson Russ Edmonston. 
</P>
<P>
 "With the aftershocks, people realize they may have more damage than they had 
with the original quake," Edmonston said. 
</P>
<P>
 Local, state and federal agencies hope the new July 18 deadline will 
accommodate any additional requests for aid, he said. 
</P>
<P>
 Those seeking assistance can apply at any of the 11 earthquake service centers 
in the Los Angeles area or by calling the registration number at 800-462-9029, 
or 800-462-7585 for the hearing or speech impaired. 
</P>
<P>
 In the San Fernando Valley, earthquake service centers are situated in 
Northridge, Sylmar, Van Nuys, Sherman Oaks and at Cal State Northridge. 
</P>
<P>
 The deadline to apply for Small Business Administration loans was also 
extended to July 18, but the Oct. 17 deadline for SBA economic injury loans 
will not be extended, according to a statement released jointly by the 
assistance agencies. 
</P>
</TEXT>
