</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Prudential Home Mortgage Co., facing a slower market for its fixed-rate loans 
with the recent rise in interest rates, laid off 57 workers at its loan 
processing center here this week as part of a 12% reduction in staff 
nationwide. 
</P>
<P>
 The layoffs at the Costa Mesa facility, one of the company's four loan 
processing centers across the nation, cut Prudential's staff here to 205, a 
spokesman for the Clayton, Mo., lender said. 
</P>
<P>
 The layoffs, announced Thursday, came with four weeks notice and a severance 
package that includes health-care benefits, outplacement help and continuation 
of other benefits for limited periods. 
</P>
<P>
 Prudential Home Mortgage, a subsidiary of Prudential Insurance Co. in Newark, 
N.J., said earlier this week that it would lay off a total of 600 workers 
systemwide. 
