<P>
DIGEST: VENTURA STOCK CARS RAINED OUT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Friday night's stock car competition at Ventura Raceway was canceled because 
of heavy rain. 
</P>
<P>
 A recording on the raceway's main telephone line said that tonight's SCRA 
sprint car program will proceed as scheduled with the gates opening at 4 p.m. 
and a 7 p.m. start for racing. 
</P>
<P>
 Track officials also advised callers to check with the pit office at 
805-648-7223 after noon for further updates, because of the threat of more 
storms. College Football  
</P>
<P>
 Cal State Northridge announced Friday its team captains for the 1994 football 
season, selecting four seniors, two from the offensive unit and two from the 
defense. 
</P>
<P>
 The four Matador captains will be quarterback J.J. O'Laughlin, offensive 
lineman Edvin Babajova, cornerback Vincent Johnson and linebacker Tony Simon. 
Miscellany  
</P>
<P>
 The Ventura County Sheriffs will play against the Ventura County Fire Dept. in 
a basketball game to raise money for the construction of a local gymnasium, 
designed to cut down on youth crime in Oxnard. 
</P>
<P>
 The game will be played at Rio Mesa High at 7 p.m. May 14. 
</P>
<P>
 Ticket prices are $4 for adults, $3 for seniors and students. Children under 
12 are free. 
</P>
<P>
 Information: Marilyn Woods, 805-656-6300. 
</P>
</TEXT>
