<HEADLINE>
<P>
SIGNINGS; CORONA DEL MAR'S HOPPE SIGNS WITH USC 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Corona del Mar volleyball player Brooks Hoppe signed Thursday with the USC, 
according to Corona del Mar Coach Joey Fuschetti. 
</P>
<P>
 Hoppe, 6 feet 4, was named to the all-Sea View League team last season. He has 
played on the U.S. Junior National Elite Training team for last two years in 
Colorado Springs, Colo. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Erik Mattern, Mater Dei shortstop, has signed a letter of intent with Arizona, 
Monarch Coach Bob Ickes said Friday. 
</P>
<P>
 Mattern, whom Ickes described as "the best player on the team," was a 
first-team All-South Coast League selection last season. 
</P>
