<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: NEWPORT BEACH; PSYCHIC FAIR CATERS TO BELIEVERS, SKEPTICS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BOB ELSTON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Palm readers, massage therapists and tarot card readers will appear at the 
three-day Psychic Faire this weekend at the Hyatt Newporter. 
</P>
<P>
 The fair, which began Friday evening and ends Sunday, caters to both believers 
and skeptics, and it will feature a wide variety of supernatural and 
astrological experiences, said Kathleen Scott, fair organizer and veteran 
astrologer. 
</P>
<P>
 Among the 18 psychic guests will be Bonita Kent, a script channeler who claims 
she can write down the words being communicated to her by the dead; Natalie 
Kahn, who draw psychic portraits, and Diana Gale, creator of the radio show 
"Tap Dancing Through the Mind." 
</P>
<P>
 Scott, who has been practicing astrology for almost 20 years and has organized 
previous psychic fairs, said she doesn't expect people to believe the power of 
psychic phenomenon until actually seeing it done firsthand. 
</P>
<P>
 "You have to see it for yourself," she said. "I have had psychics (coming to 
the fair) for their psychic readings." 
</P>
<P>
 The Hyatt Newporter is at 1107 Jamboree Road in Newport Beach. The fair's 
hours are from 11 a.m. to 8 p.m. today and from 11 a.m. to 6 p.m. Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
 For more information, call (714) 645-9900.BOB ELSTON 
</P>
</TEXT>
